-- Fitch upgrades NY state general obligation bonds to 'AA+'
-- 
-- Fri Jun 20, 2014 04:31PM EDT
-- None



June 20 (Reuters) - Fitch Ratings upgraded the rating for the State of New York's general obligation (GO) bonds to 'AA+' from 'AA', citing improved fiscal management practices by the state in recent years.

The ratings agency expects that the state will continue to adhere to strengthened fiscal management practices. (http://bit.ly/1kVVUjj)